criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        - presence of at least one implant with a pocket probing depth (PPD) ≥ 4 mm, bleeding on
        probing (BOP) or pus on probing and no radiographically detectable bone loss (Qualifying
        site).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  pregnant or lactating females;

          -  patients with severe systemic diseases, or with uncontrolled diabetes mellitus;

          -  assumption of agents affecting the periodontal status within 1 month prior to the
             study;

          -  use of systemic antibiotics within 3 months prior to the study;

          -  prophylactic antibiotics requirement;

          -  peri-implant specific treatments within 6 months prior to the study;

          -  allergy to sulphates and its derivatives.
